						<summary>

						<p>Slab in the ruined temple of Īśvara outside the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalla [Vikramāditya VI] 1104 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is worn out in parts. It mentions yuvaraja Mallikārjunadēva as the <hi rend="italic">aṇuga</hi> of the Paṭṭamahādēvi. It registers a gift of land and garden to the god Māṇikēśvara of Bammukūru. Also, it mentions <hi rend="italic">maṇḍalēśvara</hi> Nāgarasa. It refers to a measuring rod probably named after the god Māṇikēśvara.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in Chālukya Vikrama year 29, Tārana, Bhādrapada śu. 13, Sunday corresponding to 1104 A.D., September 4, Sunday f.d.t. 71.</p>						

						</summary>
